<?php
$t = array();
$t[1] = 'Blessed is He who sent down the Criterion upon His Servant that he may be to the worlds a warner -';
$t[2] = 'He to whom belongs the dominion of the heavens and the earth and who has not taken a son and has not had a partner in dominion and has created each thing and determined it with [precise] determination.';
$t[3] = 'But they have taken besides Him gods which create nothing, while they are created, and possess not for themselves any harm or benefit and possess not [power to cause] death or life or resurrection.';
$t[4] = 'And those who disbelieve say, &quot;This [Qur\'an] is not except a falsehood he invented, and another people assisted him in it.&quot; But they have committed an injustice and a lie.';
$t[5] = 'And they say, &quot;Legends of the former peoples which he has written down, and they are dictated to him morning and afternoon.&quot;';
$t[6] = 'Say, [O Muhammad], &quot;It has been revealed by He who knows [every] secret within the heavens and the earth. Indeed, He is ever Forgiving and Merciful.&quot;';
$t[7] = 'And they say, &quot;What is this messenger that eats food and walks in the markets? Why was there not sent down to him an angel so he would be with him a warner?';
$t[8] = 'Or [why is not] a treasure presented to him [from heaven], or does he [not] have a garden from which he eats?&quot; And the wrongdoers say, &quot;You follow not but a man affected by magic.&quot;';
$t[9] = 'Look how they strike for you comparisons; but they have strayed, so they cannot [find] a way.';
$t[10] = 'Blessed is He who, if He willed, could have made for you [something] better than that - gardens beneath which rivers flow - and could make for you palaces.';
$t[11] = 'But they have denied the Hour, and We have prepared for those who deny the Hour a Blaze.';
$t[12] = 'When the Hellfire sees them from a distant place, they will hear its fury and roaring.';
$t[13] = 'And when they are thrown into a narrow place therein bound in chains, they will cry out thereupon for destruction.';
$t[14] = '[They will be told], &quot;Do not cry this Day for one destruction but cry for much destruction.&quot;';
$t[15] = 'Say, &quot;Is that better or the Garden of Eternity which is promised to the righteous? It will be for them a reward and destination.';
$t[16] = 'For them therein is whatever they wish, [while] abiding eternally. It is ever upon your Lord a promise [worthy to be] requested.';
$t[17] = 'And [mention] the Day He will gather them and that which they worship besides Allah and will say, &quot;Did you mislead these, My servants, or did they [themselves] stray from the way?&quot;';
$t[18] = 'They will say, &quot;Exalted are You! It was not for us to take besides You any allies. But You provided comforts for them and their fathers until they forgot the message and became a people ruined.&quot;';
$t[19] = 'So they will deny you, [disbelievers], in what you say, and you cannot avert [punishment] or [find] help. And whoever commits injustice among you - We will make him taste a great punishment.';
$t[20] = 'And We did not send before you, [O Muhammad], any of the messengers except that they ate food and walked in the markets. And We have made some of you [people] as trial for others - will you have patience? And ever is your Lord, Seeing.';
$t[21] = 'And those who do not expect the meeting with Us say, &quot;Why were not angels sent down to us, or [why] do we [not] see our Lord?&quot; They have certainly become arrogant within themselves and [become] insolent with great insolence.';
$t[22] = 'The day they see the angels - no good tidings will there be that day for the criminals, and [the angels] will say, &quot;Prevented and inaccessible.&quot;';
$t[23] = 'And We will regard what they have done of deeds and make them as dust dispersed.';
$t[24] = 'The companions of Paradise, that Day, are [in] a better settlement and better resting place.';
$t[25] = 'And [mention] the Day when the heaven will split open with [emerging] clouds, and the angels will be sent down in successive descent.';
$t[26] = 'True sovereignty, that Day, is for the Most Merciful. And it will be upon the disbelievers a difficult Day.';
$t[27] = 'And the Day the wrongdoer will bite on his hands [in regret] he will say, &quot;Oh, I wish I had taken with the Messenger a way.';
$t[28] = 'Oh, woe to me! I wish I had not taken that one as a friend.';
$t[29] = 'He led me away from the remembrance after it had come to me. And ever is Satan, to man, a deserter.&quot;';
$t[30] = 'And the Messenger has said, &quot;O my Lord, indeed my people have taken this Qur\'an as [a thing] abandoned.&quot;';
$t[31] = 'And thus have We made for every prophet an enemy from among the criminals. But sufficient is your Lord as a guide and a helper.';
$t[32] = 'And those who disbelieve say, &quot;Why was the Qur\'an not revealed to him all at once?&quot; Thus [it is] that We may strengthen thereby your heart. And We have spaced it distinctly.';
$t[33] = 'And they do not come to you with an argument except that We bring you the truth and the best explanation.';
$t[34] = 'The ones who are gathered on their faces to Hell - those are the worst in position and farthest astray in [their] way.';
$t[35] = 'And We had certainly given Moses the Scripture and appointed with him his brother Aaron as an assistant.';
$t[36] = 'And We said, &quot;Go both of you to the people who have denied Our signs.&quot; Then We destroyed them with [complete] destruction.';
$t[37] = 'And the people of Noah - when they denied the messengers, We drowned them, and We made them for mankind a sign. And We have prepared for the wrongdoers a painful punishment.';
$t[38] = 'And [We destroyed] \'Aad and Thamud and the companions of the well and many generations between them.';
$t[39] = 'And for each We presented examples [as warnings], and each We destroyed with [total] destruction.';
$t[40] = 'And they have already come upon the town which was showered with a rain of evil. So have they not seen it? But they are not expecting resurrection.';
$t[41] = 'And when they see you, [O Muhammad], they take you not except in ridicule, [saying], &quot;Is this the one whom Allah has sent as a messenger?';
$t[42] = 'He almost would have misled us from our gods had we not been steadfast in [worship of] them.&quot; But they are going to know, when they see the punishment, who is farthest astray in [his] way.';
$t[43] = 'Have you seen the one who takes as his god his own desire? Then would you be responsible for him?';
$t[44] = 'Or do you think that most of them hear or reason? They are not except like livestock. Rather, they are [even] more astray in [their] way.';
$t[45] = 'Have you not considered your Lord - how He extends the shadow, and if He willed, He could have made it stationary? Then We made the sun for it an indication.';
$t[46] = 'Then We hold it in hand for a brief grasp.';
$t[47] = 'And it is He who has made the night for you as clothing and sleep [a means for] rest and has made the day a resurrection.';
$t[48] = 'And it is He who sends the winds as good tidings before His mercy, and We send down from the sky pure water';
$t[49] = 'That We may bring to life thereby a dead land and give it as drink to those We created of numerous livestock and men.';
$t[50] = 'And We have certainly distributed it among them that they might be reminded, but most of the people refuse except disbelief.';
$t[51] = 'And if We had willed, We could have sent into every city a warner.';
$t[52] = 'So do not obey the disbelievers, and strive against them with the Qur\'an a great striving.';
$t[53] = 'And it is He who has released [simultaneously] the two seas, one fresh and sweet and one salty and bitter, and He placed between them a barrier and prohibiting partition.';
$t[54] = 'And it is He who has created from water a human being and made him [a relative by] lineage and marriage. And ever is your Lord competent [concerning creation].';
$t[55] = 'But they worship rather than Allah that which does not benefit them or harm them, and the disbeliever is ever, against his Lord, an assistant [to Satan].';
$t[56] = 'And We have not sent you, [O Muhammad], except as a bringer of good tidings and a warner.';
$t[57] = 'Say, &quot;I do not ask of you for it any payment - only that whoever wills might take to his Lord a way.&quot;';
$t[58] = 'And rely upon the Ever-Living who does not die, and exalt [Allah] with His praise. And sufficient is He to be, with the sins of His servants, Acquainted -';
$t[59] = 'He who created the heavens and the earth and what is between them in six days and then established Himself above the Throne - the Most Merciful, so ask about Him one well informed.';
$t[60] = 'And when it is said to them, &quot;Prostrate to the Most Merciful,&quot; they say, &quot;And what is the Most Merciful? Should we prostrate to that which you order us?&quot; And it increases them in aversion.';
$t[61] = 'Blessed is He who has placed in the sky great stars and placed therein a [burning] lamp and luminous moon.';
$t[62] = 'And it is He who has made the night and the day in succession for whoever desires to remember or desires gratitude.';
$t[63] = 'And the servants of the Most Merciful are those who walk upon the earth easily, and when the ignorant address them [harshly], they say [words of] peace,';
$t[64] = 'And those who spend [part of] the night to their Lord prostrating and standing [in prayer]';
$t[65] = 'And those who say, &quot;Our Lord, avert from us the punishment of Hell. Indeed, its punishment is ever adhering;';
$t[66] = 'Indeed, it is evil as a settlement and residence.&quot;';
$t[67] = 'And [they are] those who, when they spend, do so not excessively or sparingly but are ever, between that, [justly] moderate';
$t[68] = 'And those who do not invoke with Allah another deity or kill the soul which Allah has forbidden [to be killed], except by right, and do not commit unlawful sexual intercourse. And whoever should do that will meet a penalty.';
$t[69] = 'Multiplied for him is the punishment on the Day of Resurrection, and he will abide therein humiliated -';
$t[70] = 'Except for those who repent, believe and do righteous work. For them Allah will replace their evil deeds with good. And ever is Allah Forgiving and Merciful.';
$t[71] = 'And he who repents and does righteousness does indeed turn to Allah with [accepted] repentance.';
$t[72] = 'And [they are] those who do not testify to falsehood, and when they pass near ill speech, they pass by with dignity.';
$t[73] = 'And those who, when reminded of the verses of their Lord, do not fall upon them deaf and blind.';
$t[74] = 'And those who say, &quot;Our Lord, grant us from among our wives and offspring comfort to our eyes and make us an example for the righteous.&quot;';
$t[75] = 'Those will be awarded the Chamber for what they patiently endured, and they will be received therein with greetings and [words of] peace.';
$t[76] = 'Abiding eternally therein. Good is the settlement and residence.';
$t[77] = 'Say, &quot;What would my Lord care for you if not for your supplication?&quot; For you [disbelievers] have denied, so your denial is going to be adherent.';
?>